==English==

===Noun===
#A sudden rush of creative impulse or inspiration, often attributed to divine influence.

===Etymology===

The noun shares the same root as as "flatus" meaning "wind", since it was thought that the gods blew on people, who would then inhale the god's breath and have an idea. This is the premise of "inspiration": inhaling divine breath and ideas. 

